<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1929-04-25T19:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1929-04-25T19:00:00-05:00" n="620" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d620">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">723.2515/3351: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in Peru</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Moore</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-04-25T19:00:00-05:00">April 25, 1929—7
                                p.m.</date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>47. Before answering your 81, April 24, 10 p.m., the Department would
                            like to know results of the interview between President Leguia and the
                            Chilean Ambassador regarding the scope of the suggestion of settlement
                            to be made by the President which your 80, April 24, 2 p.m.,
                            promised.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>